body: get a wallpaper steamer their very cheap or borrow one of a relative or friend and a couple of cheap wallpaper scrapers you will be able to use all this stuff in years to come so it not wasted money you say house was built in 1998 so walls should be sound just make sure you do not keep steamer in one spot too long as this may lift the plaster skim off especially we are cables are buried in the plaster keep the scraper fairly flat to the wall so you can get under the paper and not dig into the plaser once you have paper off fill any holes marks and use a bit of sandpaper wrapped round a small block of wood to sand the filler flat so it level with the rest of the wall run your palms over the full wall and sand out any raised bits that feel like a bit of grit once your happy everything is ready to paint vac all the dust up and go round the skirtings and electrical fittings with masking tape making sure you get a nice straight line along top of the skirting you should be ready to paint now matt emulsion is easiest to use a ncd covers a lot of little imperfections make sure you stir it well before you start use a small brush maybe 2inch to go along where the ceiling meets the wall do this very carefully so you get a nice straight line do the corners of the wall and go round light switches and sockets then go along the skirting you should now have a border of paint around 2inch now use a big roller to fill the rest of the wall in with paint cut in another wall while that dries once dry repeat and that should be that wall done take masking tape off as soon as you can even when second coat of paint is still damp as it will stick to the paint sometimes when it dry use a children artist brush to touch in any awkward corners or bits the masking tape has pulled off sounds like a lot of work but it will look good and it is good to learn so you can do a good job on the rest of the house when the time comes
